Okay, so avoiding complete negativity, the camera work and parkour were 
both very solid and impressive.

That said, the VFX, though obviously not an attempt at photoreal, we're 
extremely poor. And considering that they took up half the video and 
honestly I suspect little over a day or so to animate in entirety, it 
completely destroys any of the hard work and effort that went into any of 
it.

Obviously you guys get stuff right or you wouldn't be as successful as you 
are now, but I think you really need to pull your thumbs out after this 
one.﻿

I can say that all of us here at Warialasky understand why people are upset 
with the quality of this video. While we can't describe specifically what 
our process was for creating this video, we can say that we have some 
exciting changes coming to the channel soon that will really boost the 
overall quality of our content. Also, new video up now!

you guys that the joke didn't end up as good as it could have been :/

A suggestion would be to make the video a lot shorter. That would send a 
clear message that this was indeed made cheesy with the purpose of being 
humoristic. For example, the intro could have been shortened to just a few 
seconds. Throwing in more texts like at 0:19 (bottom right corner) would 
help getting that message across even more.

TL;DR = Throw more hints if you're going to make a joke like this﻿
